The article is a transcript of remarks made by President Donald Trump as he awarded the Presidential Medal of Freedom to seven recipients: Senator Orrin Hatch, Justice Antonin Scalia, Miriam Adelson, Roger Staubach, Justice Alan Page, Babe Ruth, and Elvis Presley. The President highlighted the accomplishments and contributions of each recipient, ranging from their legislative work, legal achievements, philanthropy, sports achievements, and cultural impact. The President emphasized the significance of the Medal of Freedom and praised the recipients for their outstanding contributions to American life and culture.